# Backend API Deprecation Plan
# Full removal of api.tinyhumans.ai / staging-api.tinyhumans.ai surface
# Generated: 2026-05-21
# Reviewed/updated against current tree: 2026-05-22

---

## Scope decision

Strategic decision: do **not** start a ground-up rewrite unless the product scope is
intentionally reduced to a much smaller app. The valuable hard parts in this tree
(Tauri/CEF shell, in-process core, native OAuth, credential storage, scanners,
event bus, channel runtime, memory, tests) should be kept. Treat this as a
boundary-excision migration: delete or replace every OpenHuman product-backend edge,
then enforce that boundary with greps/CI.

billing/, referral/, team/ and all backend-proxy modules are **fully removed with no replacement**.
This is a single-user local desktop. There is no subscription, no credit balance, no team, no
referral programme. The UI surfaces for those features are deleted too.

Channel delivery (Telegram, Discord, Slack, etc.) already has a fully native path in
`channels/runtime/`. The backend-proxied path in `channels/bus.rs` is deleted.
See Section 5 for the detailed native channel architecture.

Current audit notes (2026-05-22):
  - `src/openhuman/{billing,referral,team}/` are already absent in this checkout.
    Keep their plan entries as cross-branch guidance, but the live work is now
    frontend route/nav cleanup plus any stale schema/test references.
  - `src/api/` is still reachable from more places than Section 2 originally listed:
    webhook tunnel CRUD, channel managed-DM controllers, Telegram registration callback,
    Composio backend mode, cloud voice/TTS, meet-agent, and backend integration tools.
  - `composio.mode = "direct"` is documented as the fork default, but code still
    defaults to `"backend"` in `src/openhuman/config/schema/tools.rs`. Direct-only
    Composio must be a first-class phase, not a comment cleanup.

