### 1.4  src/openhuman/socket/   (~6 files, ~1,550 LOC)
The entire Socket.IO WebSocket connection to wss://api.tinyhumans.ai/socket.io.
This is the transport that delivered ChannelInboundMessage events to channels/bus.rs.
Once deleted, channels/bus.rs has no feeder and can be deleted too (Section 1.5).

Pre-deletion: move `WebhookRouter` out of `SocketManager::shared.webhook_router`.
The router currently lives here because the backend socket manager held a reference to it.
After the move, store it in a standalone global in src/openhuman/webhooks/ (a OnceLock
or similar), and update global_socket_manager().webhook_router() callers to use the
new accessor.

Files to delete once WebhookRouter is moved:
  - src/openhuman/socket/mod.rs
  - src/openhuman/socket/manager.rs         (SocketManager, global accessor, SharedState)
  - src/openhuman/socket/ws_loop.rs         (Engine.IO/Socket.IO WebSocket loop, ~680 LOC)
  - src/openhuman/socket/event_handlers.rs  (parse_sio_event, handle_sio_event, ~490 LOC)
  - src/openhuman/socket/types.rs
  - src/openhuman/socket/schemas.rs         (socket RPC schema registrations)

Also delete src/api/socket.rs (websocket_url builder only used by ws_loop).
Remove socket module from src/openhuman/mod.rs.
Remove SocketManager startup from src/core/jsonrpc.rs.

### 1.5  src/openhuman/channels/bus.rs   (+ bus_tests.rs if present)
The ChannelInboundSubscriber subscribes to DomainEvent::ChannelInboundMessage events
emitted by the backend socket. All outbound operations (send_channel_reply,
send_typing_indicator, send_filler_message, delete_channel_message, progressive edits)
call BackendOAuthClient against /channels/{channel}/messages.

This file is the backend-proxied channel path and is entirely replaced by the native
channel runtime in channels/runtime/dispatch.rs (see Section 5 for details).

Delete:
  - src/openhuman/channels/bus.rs
  - src/openhuman/channels/bus_tests.rs (if it exists separately)

Remove the ChannelInboundSubscriber registration from startup wiring.

### 1.6  src/openhuman/inference/provider/openhuman_backend.rs
OpenHumanBackendProvider routes chat via the backend /openai/v1/* proxy with session JWT.
In the fork this is dead code â€” the factory's make_openhuman_backend() already returns
an error pointing users to Settings â†’ AI. Delete the module and update the factory:

  - src/openhuman/inference/provider/openhuman_backend.rs

In src/openhuman/inference/provider/factory.rs:
  - Remove `use ... openhuman_backend::OpenHumanBackendProvider;`
  - Remove the PROVIDER_OPENHUMAN = "openhuman" constant
  - Replace make_openhuman_backend() with a direct anyhow::bail! that says:
    "No LLM provider configured. Add a provider under Settings â†’ AI."
  - Remove all `"openhuman"` sentinel branches in provider_for_role()
  - Remove the fallback `return make_openhuman_backend(config)` lines
  - In src/openhuman/inference/provider/mod.rs remove `pub mod openhuman_backend;`

### 1.7  src/openhuman/embeddings/cloud.rs
OpenHumanCloudEmbedding routes POST /openai/v1/embeddings through the backend
(Voyage-backed). Default embedder for fresh installs.

Delete: src/openhuman/embeddings/cloud.rs

Replacement: The local Ollama embedder (embeddings/ollama.rs or similar) becomes the
default. Update the embedder factory (embeddings/mod.rs or wherever the default is
selected) so that when no explicit embedding_provider is configured the app either:
  a) Falls back to the Ollama embedder (if local AI is running), or
  b) Returns a clear error: "No embedding provider configured. Enable local AI or set
     memory.embedding_provider in config.toml."

Do NOT silently fail on embed â€” the error must propagate so ingest jobs log a clear
reason for skipping the row rather than inserting empty vectors.

### 1.8  src/openhuman/memory/tree/score/embed/cloud.rs
Wraps OpenHumanCloudEmbedding for the memory tree embedder trait.
Delete after 1.7 is done.

  - src/openhuman/memory/tree/score/embed/cloud.rs

Update src/openhuman/memory/tree/score/embed/mod.rs to remove the cloud variant
from the embedder selection logic.

### 1.9  src/openhuman/integrations/client.rs  +  src/openhuman/integrations/types.rs (partial)
IntegrationClient holds `backend_url` and `auth_token` and is the shared HTTP client for
backend-proxied integration tools. It is not only WebSearchTool:
  - Composio backend-mode client (`src/openhuman/composio/client.rs`)
  - Apify-backed LinkedIn enrichment (`src/openhuman/learning/linkedin_enrichment.rs`)
  - Parallel search/extract/chat/research/enrich/dataset
  - Google Places, Twilio, stock/financial APIs
  - `/agent-integrations/pricing`

  - Delete or gut src/openhuman/integrations/client.rs
  - Remove the BackendResponse / IntegrationPricing types that are backend-envelope-specific
  - Keep any types that are reusable (SearchResultItem etc) if a replacement search is added
  - Do this only after Composio is direct-only (Section 3.14) and each non-Composio
    integration tool is either replaced with a direct BYO-key implementation or removed.

### 1.10  src/openhuman/tools/impl/network/web_search.rs
WebSearchTool routes search through the backend's Parallel integration proxy.
With IntegrationClient gone this file is dead.

Options (choose one):
  a) Wire a direct search API (Brave Search API, SerpAPI, or Tavily) behind a user-configured
     API key. Simplest: Brave's `https://api.search.brave.com/res/v1/web/search` requires
     only a `X-Subscription-Token` header and returns JSON. Add `brave_search_api_key` to
     the config and route through that when present.
  b) Remove the tool entirely and deregister it from the orchestrator tools list.

Do NOT leave a stub that silently returns empty results. If option (b) is chosen,
remove the `web_search` / `gitbooks_search` tool registrations from tool schemas,
tool registry, and agent TOML references (`help`, `welcome`, `planner`, `researcher`)
as applicable. If `gitbooks_search` is kept, it must use a local/static docs index or
a direct user-configured search provider, not the backend Parallel proxy.

### 1.11  src/openhuman/integrations/* backend-proxied tools
These modules are backend-product integration proxies, not native desktop integrations:
  - src/openhuman/integrations/apify.rs
  - src/openhuman/integrations/parallel.rs
  - src/openhuman/integrations/google_places.rs
  - src/openhuman/integrations/stock_prices.rs
  - src/openhuman/integrations/twilio.rs
  - src/openhuman/integrations/test_support.rs and related tests

For each tool family choose one:
  a) Replace with a direct provider API and user-owned key in config/AuthService
     (Apify token, Parallel key, Google Places key, Alpha Vantage/market-data key,
     Twilio Account SID/Auth Token, etc.), or
  b) Remove the tool type, schema/registry entry, agent TOML reference, and tests.

Do not keep backend-metered pricing text or `/agent-integrations/*` paths. Once this
phase is done, `src/openhuman/integrations/mod.rs` should no longer describe a backend
proxy layer, and `build_client()` should be gone.

